By Kingsley Nwezeh Governor of Ekiti State, Kayode Fayemi, Minister of Defence, Major General Bashir Magashi (rtd), service chiefs and senior military officers are attending the burial of seven Air Force personnel, who died in a plane crash in Abuja. <img src="https://i0.wp.com/storage.googleapis.com/thisday-846548948316-wp-data/wp-media/e70bdfd2-air-force-personnel-burial-3.gif?w=696&#038;ssl=1" data-recalc-dims="1" /> Family members of the fallen officers are also attending the burial. <img src="https://i1.wp.com/storage.googleapis.com/thisday-846548948316-wp-data/wp-media/560132ee-air-force-personnel-burial-1.gif?w=696&#038;ssl=1" data-recalc-dims="1" /> Also at the ongoing burial ceremony are Chairmen of the National Assembly Committees on Defence, Senator Ibn Na’lla and Hon Shehu Diko and Minister of Women Affairs, Mrs Pauline Tallen. <img src="https://i0.wp.com/storage.googleapis.com/thisday-846548948316-wp-data/wp-media/e5812e49-air-force-personnel-burial-2.gif?w=696&#038;ssl=1" data-recalc-dims="1" />  Details later…